                <div class="news-description">
                    <div class="news-id">ann1708 — Announcement</div>
                    <div class="news-title">May issue of ESA/Hubble Science Newsletter now available</div>
                    <div class="news-teaser"><strong>18 May 2017</strong>: The May 2017 issue of the ESA/Hubble Science Newsletter is now available, bringing information and interviews about the successful travelling exhibition Our Place in Space and an overview of the press releases produced by ESA/Hubble in 2016. Further topics include the latest improvements on the European Hubble archive eHST and a look back on the latest Science with the Hubble Space Telescope conference, which took place in Venice earlier this year. The ESA/Hubble Science Newsletter promotes technical and operational news for the Hubble Space Telescope to European users and the scientific community. It is also intended to create a communication channel between the European Hubble user community, and the staff scientists at ESA who support Hubble science operations. You can subscribe to the ESA/Hubble Science Newsletter here, or get in touch at hubblenewseurope@stsci.edu. If you are a media representative we recommend subscribing to the ESA/Hubble Media Newsletter, a weekly embargoed …</div>
